<!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
LDONs have become invaluable training groups for pulling, I think. Start with a normal, bring yourself a good group that can deal with adds. Once you learn to use lull to pull (which is amazingly easy, lull everything but the one you want to pull), take the spell out of your line up and try hard to get singles. Eventually move to hard LDONs where you couldn't use lull if you wanted to. Once you're semi-capable of staying alive in a hard LDON (I say semi because in a raid setting, you have a lot more support if you fuck up) have at those raid pulls.<br>
<br>
Outdoor zones are our playground. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Impresario <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=895220">Bremel</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - 65 Maestro of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.stasis-guild.com" target="top">Stasis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
The artist formerly known as Farlander</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dsavereide>dsavereide</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(6/2/04 6:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallcenterstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bard VT pulling</span><hr size=1> It's may be too late, but I didn't see this question in January. VT is great for bard pullers and I'm the main puller there for my guild. No pacifies, but bards have some big advantages there over other classes for pulling.<br>
<br>
VT is full of casters and many AE casters. Spells don't break fade they way they do feign. Tagging in the vicinity of a feigned monk can get him killed if the mob stops to cast an AE. And fade gets you instantly off the aggro list, no waiting for mobs to return to spawn or a two minute timer to expire. Important because mobs there don't always path back to their spawn directly, they take a stroll and visit friends. A monk getting up at the wrong time can bring back more mobs then he started with.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of traps that spawn mobs when you step on them. You can get an SoS rogue to pre-spring the traps for you (though this will result in an occasional rogue death), or you can selos, run in and out again since there is some delay in the spawn. Never attempt recovery in a trap room. Traps respawn much more quickly than the other mobs. Twenty minutes vs two hours or about that.<br>
<br>
Many see invis mobs. More than not. So you need to allow yourself room to split. Casters will help the split a lot because they are standing there nuking you while the melee are on your heels. Selos and PoV - always up when pulling. Mezz seems to have a lower aggro range and so can be used to split as long as you fade before mezz breaks. <br>
<br>
Aggro range is huge there as is assist range. Its fairly easy to chain aggro a dozen or more mobs. You can pull through some doors just by standing in front of them or the moment you open them. Spell Awareness Leadership AA is a big help here, because you can spot when you have aggro before getting whacked. I use DA song when aggro pulling a lot It seems to reduce the range a bit and keeps me alive. It also saves an initial fade.<br>
<br>
Know how many mobs your group can handle. Qua's and Zov's are mezzable. The rest all need off tanks. Except for the nameds (and sometimes even then) you are not trying to single pull... you are trying to bring the mobs in manageable chunks. Obviously this will depend on how many and what classes you have. And how dicsiplined they are.<br>
<br>
If you don't have the bellow AA, get it. A 250 range insta-cast lure is fantastic when you have to time the tag just right. Put up two junk buffs that you can refresh yourself. Many casters will turn on you even after a tank has aggro just to debuff you.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oomoseoo>oo Mose oo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(6/3/04 8:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallcenterstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard VT pulling</span><hr size=1> as just a general statement on pulling...<br>
<br>
