<br>
Problem you might get is one out of two as far as re-aggro is concerned.<br>
<br>
1) The mobs you tried to Fade off see invis, and are still within aggro range, and will reaggro you promptly.<br>
<br>
2) One of the mobs you Faded off was in the middle of a cast, and when it lands it breaks your invis and reaggroes whatever you pulled.<br>
<br>
Other than those two problems, you can use FM just as a nec/sk or monk pulls with FD. Only problem is your mana takes long to replace, so several Fades will leave you manaless and &quot;fade-less&quot;. I usually use the &quot;FD pull&quot; technique with FM when I need to get a named mob to the group and there are too many other mobs to bother about.<br>
<br>
Pull 'em all, Fade, tag the named as mobs have walked off. Takes a lil luck is all in regard to which mobs walk off first hehe.<br>
<br>
As for pulling in LDoN, or anywhere for that matter...<br>
<br>
Lull whatever is close enough to the mob you want for them to add on you. How to figure out how far away is safe to not lull, just lull all except the one you think might be safe and pull your mob, see if he aggroes. If he does, you'll have a pointer on how far they have to be not to aggro.<br>
<br>
Pull with Requiem of Time if you know whats good for you.<br>
<br>
1) Requiem of Time is a no-dmg song, hence the mobs arent &quot;allowed&quot; to summon you during the pull.<br>
<br>
2) If it lands, which they usually do on regular exp grind groups, its 54% slowed right of the bat, meaning less pain for you if the tank dont grab aggro off you quick.<br>
<br>
I only ever have a need for FM in Hard LDoN's. In regular ones adds arent a problem. Usually try not to get any adds, but they arent much more than a nauscience if you know to do your mezzing role properly.<br>
<br>
In hards however, its the adds that will kill the group. You pull singles on a hard adventure and it will be a cakewalk. Even had a druid not know we were doing a hard adventure until we were halfway through it and she got a punch cause she landed her heal just as the tank Incited the mob I pulled hehe. <br>
<br>
With pulling there is only one way to get good. Practice, Practice, Practice.<br>
<br>
Biggest reason I feel safe as a puller though, is because I know if we get adds I can fade, and I know my skills within mezzing are good enough to quickly lock down 3-4 adds unless unfortunate with their resist checks against my mez.<br>
<br>
Learn your skillz and practice them &quot;)<br>
<br>
Enadil Elvensinger<br>
65th Maestro of Tunare<br>
