<br>
However, some times a bard pulls better and sometimes a monk pulls better.  Bards get more tools with snare, mez and heck DA also (not just fade / lull) then monk.  And at least sometimes a bard pulls faster with sellos and I doubt your going to get a bard putting sellos up whenever you want as a monk :P.  Monks definately do better with undead in that undead dont see through FD like they do with MF.  <br>
<br>
Regardless back to the topic at hand your end statement was ok.  I think everyone should strive to be the best puller they can and a lot is just learning the mobs, how they react, what spells land on them, the pathing etc etc.  Dont try to take the pulling job away from someone who is perfectly qualified and is already doing a good job.  With a lot of pulls you can do a lot more with someone teaming with you - whether its a monk, SK, necro or another bard.<br>
<br>
VT specifically we always had monks pull in my guild so I can't give you help there.  But I like to try and minimize use of fade if possible.  Often you can use simple proximity aggro to get singles where you would get 2+ with tagging a mob directly.  LDoN's are some easy to get pulling practice.  Otherwise as a VT guild soon your be elemental and some raids do really well with bard pulls.  Your best bet is to practice as much as possible and talk to the other pulers in your guild about mob quirks in different zones.<br>
<br>
In certain places about any class makes a decent puller.  The thing with the FD classes and bards is that you have a method of ditching aggro most do not. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub26.ezboard.com/borderofthescatteredwinds">~OSW~</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=141580"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.smart-code.net/pictures/sigs/Que_sig4.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://24.26.194.253/">Avatar by Lyss</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#330000>- </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall>The Concert Hall - Message Boards</a><font color=#330000> - </font><a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallcenterstage>Center Stage</a><font color=#330000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.31p<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  